        "id": 269378,
        "name": "Thomas",
        "username": "thomas533",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/thomas533/{size}/52479_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-06-06T15:56:04.668Z",
        "cooked": "<p>A SOS message isnâ€™t the only thing that this can be used for. My kid also takes public transit home from school and we could use this to see if she is getting held up in traffic and to figure out when to go pick her up from the bus stop. I could also see this being used for variety of activities from hiking to capture the flag games. There are lots of other possibilities.</p>\n<p>And including GPS was only one way this could be used. You could do other things like including a 5 second sound or video clip. Or maybe you are an old school war driver and want a quick way to share wireless networks your device sees. This function could automate the sharing of any sort of sensor or device data.</p>\n<p>And sure, I am am aware that there are SMS solutions for this, but most of us use signal instead of SMS for many reasons. As far as broadcasting locations go, I can imagine many reasons why I might not want that going across unencrypted channels.</p>\n<p>If your suggestion is just to use SMS, then what is the point of even having Signal?</p>",
